Step 1: Identify Total Liabilities and Total Assets at the end of the reporting period.  
• Total Liabilities (end amount) come from Total Current Liabilities = 1,548,001.20  
• Total Assets (end amount) = 15,653,266.97  

Step 2: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio using the formula:  
  Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  

Step 3: Substituting the values:  
  Debt to Asset Ratio = 1,548,001.20 / 15,653,266.97 ≈ 0.0989  
Rounded to two decimal places, the ratio is approximately 0.10.

Thus, the solution in JSON format is:
{"solution": {'Debt to Asset Ratio': '0.10'}}
